2026-04-16 12:10:50 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['control module 6'] hypothesis_explanation='Control module 6 is wired incorrectly / incompletely on its + line. The observation shows that Control Input Cable (+) 6 is connected from module 5 only at its ‘p’ end, with its ‘n’ end floating, and that this floating ‘n’ was supposed to go to Switch 6. Instead, the switch’s ‘p’ port is empty, Control Output Cable (+) 6 is looped back onto itself and then on to Control Input (+) 7. This means the series + conductor from the power supply is open at module 6’s input, so no current can reach modules 6–8 or the load, which explains why the lamp and all control‑module indicators are off. The missing indicator LED in module 6 is a secondary symptom of the same mis‑assembly. Repairing/re‑wiring control module 6 so that Input (+) 6 goes through Switch 6 to Output (+) 6 (with the indicator LED/resistor correctly across + and −) should restore continuity and allow the lamp to operate when all switches are ON.'
